<br>
Then she stopped the small group..raising a hand up.  She could hear thundering hooves not far from them. Cocking a brow, Hippolyte looked to Anippe.  With a flick of her wrist and just a look, she had sent Anippe on to check out the noise.  The amazons sat silently upon their horses.  It was not long before Anippe returned and rode up beside her Queen.  <br>
<br>
&quot;It is our Northern Athelfi, my Vasilissa,&quot; she reported in a hushed voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;Very well, let us join Alysia's army,&quot; Hippolyte spoke and then nodded to those who had remained with her.  The amazons quickly rode in the direction of Alysia's tribe.<br>
<br>
As they reached them, the band stopped as Hippolyte gave a signal to the warriors of Alysia's tribe that they were truly Amazons.  Then she urged her mare and rode up to Alysia.  Dropping her reigns, she saluted her athelfi.  &quot;Yasoo, Alysia. I am sorry it has taken so long.. I hope we have not missed much,&quot; Hipp gathered a crooked grin as her brown orbs twinkled at Alysia. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ualysiaofscynthia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alysia of Scynthia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#993300>(8/21/01 5:13:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Approaching her Athelfi . . . </span><hr size=1> Alysia rode her white mare up to the Themiscryan Warriors. She had pure hatred in her eyes. She wasn't the same Aly that Eli had made her.  Her war paint was thin as she pulled her mask down and nodded to Delilah and Hippolyte.<br>
<br>
&quot;I have a feeling that we won't be the ones attacking. Nevertheless, we keep riding.&quot;<br>
<br>
Alysia was full of hate and pain. This kind of Darkness hadn't risen in her since she rode with Livia, or perhaps the first Centaur war that took place near Themiscrya. Where she and Dawn fought along side eachother. <br>
<br>
She looked back towards her other sisters.<br>
