<br>
She turned her horse to face her army of athelfi before she spoke. <br>
<br>
&quot;I want those of you who doubt yourselves to turn back now.&quot;<br>
<br>
She had true hate in her eyes. Those who knew her when she was younger, could see the old Alysia returning. Every moment, she was becomming more and more like the Samsara that she was.<br>
<br>
&quot;Our sisters have been killed! And I want vengeance!&quot; She yelled.<br>
<br>
She looked at Gabrielle sadly, and sighed remembering her fallen sisters at Helicon. She had hoped Gabrielle wouldn't mind Alysia repeating the speach at Helicon. She felt it was needed, encouragement was needed here.<br>
<br>
&quot;Our fallen sisters, our foremother, their blood was shed by the Saurian scum. Our sisters have died but death is not an end to their spirits.  Death it's a pathway to an afterlife.  And when it is my time to join them I want to know that I can grasp them by the hands I can look them all in the eyes and tell them that their blood was not shed without purpose that we finished the job that they began.  More of us may die today but the Amazon nation it will live on forever.  That is the duty that we carry and the everlasting honor that we will hold.&quot;<br>
<br>
She stopped briefly and sighed.<br>
<br>
&quot;Amazons, it is time to avenge our fallen sisters. Death to the Saurians!&quot; <br>
