Belle just sighed softly as she listened to her brother and her best friend talk, eyes locked before her on her athelfi and their destination.<br>
<br>
The usually talkative girl hadn't said a word since she, Wulf, and Cyane had left their camping trip. She couldn't manage. <br>
<br>
She gathered herself, and her mixed emotions, just enough to shoot Cy a gentle, confident smile.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm scared too, but we're all going to fine. And the Amazons will always prevail, including today.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ulatraariah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LaTra Ariah</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=C:\America Online 6.0\download\moonicon.bmp BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#993300>(8/22/01 10:42:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ariah Arrives</span><hr size=1>      It had taken Ari longer than she thought. Her horse had sprained her ankle about three fourths of the way to Scynthia and she had to continue the rest of the way on foot. She's dressed in full combat gear. She wears a sword on a sheath on her back, one at her side and daggers are sheathed in numerous places, hidden and out in the open. She wears Ephesian war paint on her face and arms.<br>
     From person to person she glances, recognizing most of the Amazons, with a few new faces until finally she spots Alysia and runs over to her.<br>
     "Aysia! I'm sorry it took me so long to get here, but I'm ready for action. What do you need me to do?" <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uyoungevelyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Young Evelyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#993300>(8/22/01 11:40:14 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/evelynsaphros/images/evelyn-5.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> O.o</span><hr size=1> Evelyn took her attention off of Delilah long enough to look around.She saw all the amazons in thier war gear and masks,and somehow could feel the intensity of the situation around her.There hadn't been any fighting yet,but already Evelyn was wondering if she wanted to be here.Absent mindedly she stroked Scoobys big head,it made her feel safe that Scooby was there,though he was big and clumsy,he always seemed to protect her when she needed it.She also felt safe being with Delilah,even though Del had so quickly shown up and swepts her up on a very large tiger,which surprisingly had no problem with Scooby,and Scooby had no problem with the tiger.Strange.<br>
<br>
Getting tired of grasping her wooden sword,she slips it into the small belt around her waist.She then glances up at Delilah,then looks around again.Her eyes stopping when she sees Ariah pass by.&quot;Ariah!&quot;She yells,but it would probley be unheared with the noise of all the horses trotting around.And she pointed to Ariah as she looked up again at Delilah.<br>
