<br>
She noticed to whom the girl was pointing. &quot;Yes... LaTra Ariah. Noble and brave,&quot; saying it loud enough for Evelyn to hear over the galloping horses. &quot;Here Evelyn, drink this. Don't want you dehydrated.&quot; She held out a wineskin full of cold, thirst-quenching water that happened to materialize in Delilah's grasp out of.. thin air. &quot;We'll be there very soon and I mustn't have you thirsty. Hold onto the wineskin and drink when needed. I will have you hidden some place safe nearby. You may not feel very fond of war after this one. I assure you, if you don't want to watch when it happens, you may close your eyes and sleep. Trust me.. you'll be fine.&quot; Her warm smile was reassuring, though her thoughts were on other things.<br>
<br>
This ride certainly wasn't a bumpy one since her tiger's sprint was very much like a glide, quite comfortable. She reached out and patted Scooby's head. &quot;You have a good companion, little girl.&quot; She clicked her tongue and her tiger sped up just a bit more. The tiger didn't look like it'd be getting tired anytime soon.<br>
<br>
